// Bone tumor - Characterization II - I describe


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I select 'Yes' radio button from Contrast enhanced box in Page 03
And	I'm on Page 04 - Bones of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
And I select ' Bone tumor' from the Finding dropdown
And I select 'I describe' radio button if not selected
And I select 'Characterization II' tab

Then 'Periostal reaction ("sun burst")' checkbox is enabled
And 'Codman triangle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Cartilage cap' checkbox is enabled
And 'Sclerotic rim' checkbox is enabled
And 'Low signal of the rim (perichondrium over cartilage cap)' checkbox is enabled

And 'Lobulated' checkbox is enabled
And 'Round' checkbox is enabled
And 'Geographic appearance' checkbox is enabled
And 'Broad-based' checkbox is enabled
And 'Pedunculated' checkbox is enabled
And 'Projecting away from the epiphysis' checkbox is enabled

And 'Osteolytic' checkbox is enabled
And 'Osteoblastic' checkbox is enabled
And 'Expansive' checkbox is enabled
And 'Sclerotic' checkbox is enabled
And 'Infiltration soft tissue' checkbox is enabled
And 'Infiltration adjacent bone' checkbox is enabled
And 'Pathological fracture' checkbox is enabled

And 'Soft tissue edema' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bone marrow edema' checkbox is enabled
And 'Perifocal sclerosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Surrounding inflammatory reaction' checkbox is enabled

And 'Another lesion, same entity' checkbox is enabled
And 'Pathological fracture' checkbox is enabled

And 'sss' radio button is enabled
And 'sss' radio button is enabled

And 'Round' checkbox is enabled

And 'Differential diagnosis 1' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Another lesion, same entity' checkbox
Then 'Within the primarily involved bone' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Histologically proven' checkbox
Then 'Benign' radio button is enabled
And 'Malignant' radio button is enabled
